        "#### Theory:\n",
        "        \n",
        "Pi (π): Pi (π) is a mathematical constant that represents the ratio of the circle’s circumference (the distance around it) to its diameter (the distance across it through the center).\n",
        "\n",
        "π=\"Circumference\" /\"Diameter\"\n",
        "\n",
        "Its approximately value is: π≈3.141592653….\n",
        "\n",
        "Pi is an irrational number because it cannot be expressed as a fraction (a/b), where b ≠ 0. Its decimal digits continue forever without repeating.\n",
        "\tPi is nonterminating and non-recurring decimal number.\n",
        "\n"
      ]
