        "## Monte Carlo Method\n",
        "\n",
        "The **Monte Carlo method** is a simulation technique that uses **random numbers** to solve mathematical problems. It estimates the value of Pi (π) by generating random points inside a square containing an inscribed circle.\n",
        "\n",
        "### Steps to Estimate Pi\n",
        "\n",
        "1. Draw a square with an inscribed circle.\n",
        "2. Generate a large number of random points inside the square.\n",
        "3. Count the number of points that fall inside the circle.\n",
        "4. Calculate the value of Pi using the following formula:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\pi \\approx \\frac{\\text{Number of points inside the circle}}{\\text{Total number of random points}}\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n"
      ]
